  "time_ut": 1657640341,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dda \u0d86\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dbb \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Measures are being taken to protect the presidential palace",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Director General of Archaeology, Professor Anura Manatunga has issued a statement saying that due to the events of the last 9th, archaeological monuments including the President's House in Colombo have been damaged and legal action will have to be taken in accordance with the Antiquities Ordinance Act.",
        "He has mentioned that in order to prevent further damage to the old monuments located in those places and to protect valuable ancient and cultural properties, appropriate actions were taken with the security officials and the parties leading the struggle, and the officials of the department will continue to regularly inspect those places.",
        "As the Director General of Archaeology, it has come to my special attention as the Director General of Archeology that due to the events that took place on the 9th and the subsequent circumstances, the archaeological monuments including the President's House in Colombo have been damaged and the ancient and cultural objects in those places should be prevented from being further destroyed or misplaced. referred to",
        "Thus, at the first possible opportunity, our officials have taken maximum measures to protect the valuable objects in those places. Today (July 12), I personally inspected the damaged places of the President's House, the President's Secretariat and the Araliyagaha Mandir along with the Additional Secretary (Heritage Division) of the Ministry of Religious and Cultural Affairs of the Buddha Sasana (Heritage Division) and the relevant officials of the Archeology Department.",
        "Appropriate measures were taken with the security personnel and parties leading the struggle to prevent further damage to the ancient monuments located in those places and to protect the valuable ancient and cultural properties. The officers of our department will continue to check those places regularly.",
        "I hereby emphasize that to avoid damaging or stealing monuments and antiquities which are public property and the nation's heritage, legal action will have to be taken in accordance with the Antiquities Ordinance. Furthermore, I remind you that protecting national heritage is the responsibility and duty of the general public."
      ],
